headline: T-Mobile wireless subscriber growth misses estimates as competition heats up
summary: Bellevue, Washington-based T-Mobile added 495,000 monthly bill-paying customers in the first three months of 2025, more than AT&T's additions, while Verizon lost subscribers in the period after warning of a hit from "off-season promotions."  To shield its market share, T-Mobile's prepaid unit earlier this week unveiled four new plans that provide a five-year price guarantee and monthly charges as low as $25 per line.  The final pricing for the satellite service would be $10 a month — down from the $15 monthly price it had announced in February — and T-Mobile will maintain that price for at least a year, CEO Mike Sievert said on a call with analysts.
